+/// inequality `sum(r²_i / dist²_i) ≤ sum(r²_i) / min(dy²_i)`: if the nearest
+/// ball is far enough vertically, the entire row is provably dark and skipped.
+/// Cost: one `min` reduction over `balls_len` per row with zero divisions.
